Section 2. R.S. 33:5052 and 5053 are hereby repealed in their entirety.
Section 3. The Louisiana State Law Institute is directed to study the prescription of
actions to enforce zoning, subdivision, and land use regulations by political subdivisions in
light of the recent decisions in McCormick v. Ford (La. 5/9/2025), 408 So.3d 932, and
Bossier Parish Policy Jury v. Hicks, (La. App. 2 Cir., 11/19/2025), 425 So.3d 252, and
propose legislation that balances the public purpose of regulating land use and the right of
property owners not to be deprived of property without due process of law and just
compensation.
Section 4. The provisions of this Act shall have prospective application only.
